post_text:
Dear Nell Holcomb Families,
Today after 5 long months, we welcomed our students and staff back to Nell Holcomb. The morning was filled with some nervous anticipation as most first days of school are. However, the students were welcomed back by some super excited and smiling teachers and staff members. We have been preparing for August 24th for weeks and now that this day is almost over, it is nice to take a few moments to reflect on what this daily truly meant for our students and the Nell Holcomb Community. Day 1 is in the books and was a huge success. There is no doubt that the 2020-2021 school year will have bumps and turns along the road. However, I am confident that with our team, anything is possible! I am so proud of our teachers and staff and the hard work they have put in to make Day One a great one!
WAY TO GO Nell Holcomb! We Got This!
Mr. D

post_text: Nell Holcomb R-IV is excited to announce that recently, we secured a grant to purchase 200 chrome books for our students. This was a goal the school had for the next 5 years, which we will now be able to accomplish this year. This is a huge step towards getting a device into the hands of each student and ensuring they are prepared for high school when leaving Nell Holcomb! There are many positive things happening at Nell Holcomb R-IV. Stay tuned!

post_text: Nell Holcomb R-IV is excited to announce the purchase of 3 new school buses for the 2020-2021 school year. The community supported us with Prop Hawks and we are proud to deliver on one of our main promises. The new buses will arrive in August and will be ready to transport students on the first day of school. We are also currently working on technology improvements, safety, and improvements on student learning. Look for more details to come in the near future! And, thank you once again for your support on Prop Hawks 2020!

post_text: Tomorrow Nell Holcomb Voters will vote on the future of Nell Holcomb School! A YES on Prop Hawks is for safety, new school buses, technology to prepare our students for high school, improved math, science, and communication arts programs, and keeping our buildings and grounds updated and beautiful. Prop Hawks is a generational plan for Nell Holcomb R-IV. It ensures that our children will enjoy this community school for decades to come. Please vote YES and share and LIKE this post. Tomorrow is the day! Spread the word to all you know! YES on Prop Hawks!

post_text: Next week, the Nell Holcomb Community will vote on PROP HAWKS! The current and future students at Nell Holcomb R-IV need your YES vote now more than ever! Last week, the governor announced more massive cuts to public school education over the next 6 months. They are cutting more dollars for transportation, safety, and student learning. PROP HAWKS is a way to offset some of these cuts and to keep Nell Holcomb an awesome place to learn and grow! Please vote YES next Tuesday.

School shouldn’t have ended like this but we are grateful for our parents, students, and staff for this opportunity to see them because we ALL needed that. 💛🖤💛🖤

A post from our favorite librarian, Mrs. Nelson:
Hope all is well! I wanted to let you know that we have a new online resource that could be really helpful for you as you're working to engage your children at home. It's a company called "Lightbox" that makes K-12 multimedia curriculum-based ebooks available at no cost and it's available until August 1! Each Lightbox ebook contains videos, activities, quizzes, links to webpages and more, making learning fun for your students of all ages!

post_text:
From Coach:

NHS families, hope everyone is safe and well ! It’s been a weird couple of weeks to say the least. I’m sure the gamers are having the time of their life ! But as I sometimes tell the students, “Life is not a video game, if you don’t get out there you’re going to miss out”. Besides the homework packets I hope the kids are staying busy and active. I sent a few things home for fitness and there’s ton of ideas online. For the b ballers you can always work on your ball handling and dribbling in the garage or if you have a driveway/carport. Shooting baskets can get boring quickly so get creative. Shoot from different spots, work on shooting off your dribble, use a dribble move then shoot. Work on your free throws !!! Use your imagination and pretend you are playing another person or team and create a game within your shooting practice.
Go on a hike, walk the dog, find a short work out video....wear those helmets and protective gear when on your dirt bike or four wheeler knuckle heads !! Hope to see the kids soon ! Stay safe, stay awesome.
Coach

We have received a few messages asking about the re-start date for the COVID-19 Shutdown. Today Cape and Jackson Schools announced they would remain closed until after the Easter Break. Our Board and Administration will be discussing on Monday to make our final decision, but all indications are pointing towards our shutdown being extended as well. We will update you as soon as we have official word on Monday. Hang in there! Stay safe, healthy, and try to keep smiling!
Mr. D

post_text:
PROP HAWKS ELECTION MOVED TO JUNE! Today, Governor Parsons signed an executive order postponing the April election until June 2nd due to the COVID-19 shutdowns. Over the next couple days, our committee will work to take down our signs so the date can be changed. Our signs will go back up in a few weeks.
One thing will not change over the next 3 months, and that is the importance to pass Proposition HAWKS for the students at Nell Holcomb. In fact, the need will only increase as our budget is certain to be impacted due to the shutdown over COVID-19. For now, be safe and take care of your families.

post_text:
The NED Show is coming to Nell Holcomb tomorrow for an assembly. The NED Show is based on Growth Mindset and is a character education program. The NED program will present their positive mindset assembly with storytelling, humor, illusions and amazing yo-yo tricks. This program uses the yo-yo as both a mindset tool and a tangible reminder of NED's message. While learning to yo-yo, children will make mistakes, try again and improve. Yo-yos will be on sale from March 17-23 from 7:30-7:55 am at the concession stand by the gym. Prices range from $8 for a classic yo-yo to a specialty one for $15.

https://www.thenedshows.com/

Proposition Hawks is about so many things! Most importantly, it is about the future of our most prized possessions (our children). Providing our children with the best education possible is our goal and Proposition Hawks is a future plan to guarantee that. Prop Hawks includes upgrades to math, science, and technology and it ensures the community that the class sizes will stay small at Nell Holcomb. Less students in each class means more attention and one on one time for each child!
Please help our students and support Prop Hawks on April 7th!

post_text:
PROP HAWKS = SCHOOL BUS UPGRADES! Each day, six Nell Holcomb school buses travel over 400 miles delivering our children to school and taking them home every evening. We have a fantastic team of drivers and our mechanic (Jody Haupt) does an amazing job keeping our buses maintained. However, like any vehicle, age along with wear and tear have taken a toll on our bus fleet. This year we have experienced multiple breakdowns, sometimes leaving our students and drivers stranded until help arrives.
We have a plan to fix that! Proposition Hawks will allow Nell Holcomb to immediately purchase two new school buses in 2020 and includes a plan to roll over our entire fleet within 5 years!
Your support guarantees safe travel for Nell Holcomb students!
Please like and share if you feel that reliable up to date school buses is a priority for our children!

post_text: One of the students’ favorite games is: thisissand. It’s a creative playground for making pictures out of sand. The sound is literally sand falling and they claim that it is “so satisfying.” Even when given the choice of a so called “fun game” or sand, so many students choose this simple, therapeutic, creative, and relaxing tool. It’s great for mouse control too. 😁
